# AI Agent & MCP Conventions

## Architecture
The AI system has two layers:
1. **WebSocket layer** (`src/agents/`) — manages client connections, streams responses
2. **MCP layer** (`src/mcp/`) — exposes tools/resources that the AI agent can call

```
client (WS) ←→ Agent (WS handler) ←→ OpenAI SDK ←→ MCP Client ←→ MCP Server (tools)
```

## WebSocket Entry
- WebSocket server runs on a **separate port** from the HTTP API
- Connection handler in `src/agents/`
- Auth: validated on WS connection upgrade

## MCP Tool Definition Pattern
```js
// src/mcp/tools/<tool-name>.js
module.exports = {
  name: 'get_brands',
  description: 'Retrieve a list of brands from the database',
  inputSchema: {
    type: 'object',
    properties: {
      search: { type: 'string', description: 'Filter by name' },
    },
  },
  handler: async (input) => {
    const brands = await brandService.queryBrands({ search: input.search });
    return { content: [{ type: 'text', text: JSON.stringify(brands) }] };
  },
};
```

## MCP Resource Definition Pattern
```js
// src/mcp/resources/<resource-name>.js
module.exports = {
  uri: 'logico://system/context',
  name: 'System Context',
  description: 'Current system configuration and context',
  mimeType: 'application/json',
  handler: async () => {
    const context = await systemService.getSystemContext();
    return JSON.stringify(context);
  },
};
```

## Registering Tools/Resources
- Register tools in `src/mcp/server.js` (the MCP server instance)
- Register resources alongside tools in the same file
- The MCP client (`src/mcp/client.js`) connects to the server via in-process transport

## OpenAI Integration
- Model is configurable via env (`OPENAI_MODEL`)
- SDK: `openai` npm package
- Streaming responses are forwarded to the client via WebSocket

## Global Context
- `src/config/global-context.js` provides system-wide context injected into AI prompts
- Updated when system settings change; refresh via the `systemContext` Zustand store on client

## Adding a New AI Tool
1. Create `src/mcp/tools/<tool-name>.js` following the pattern above
2. Import and register in `src/mcp/server.js`
3. The agent will automatically discover and use it via the MCP protocol
4. Add appropriate error handling — tools should return error content, not throw
